data-flex-basis="426px"
>
For Windows, it&amp;rsquo;s recommended to use the setup.exe file for installation instead of the msi. It will also check for any missing software required for your PC environment.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Click &amp;ldquo;Next&amp;rdquo; through all the installation prompts.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="setup-on-your-gaming-pc-steam-host">Setup on your Gaming PC (Steam Host)
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m01s028.webp"
width="1920"
height="1080"
srcset="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m01s028_hu_e137fe04a004cff7.webp 480w, https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m01s028_hu_a5eda457aaea0e54.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Enable Steam Link Remote Play"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>
Go to &amp;ldquo;Steam&amp;rdquo; -&amp;gt; &amp;ldquo;Settings&amp;rdquo; -&amp;gt; &amp;ldquo;Remote Play&amp;rdquo; -&amp;gt; and toggle &amp;ldquo;Enable Remote Play&amp;rdquo; to ON.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m12s511.webp"
width="1920"
height="1080"
srcset="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m12s511_hu_f99f19eec4acd1fe.webp 480w, https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m12s511_hu_c85f4887e28e29f5.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Add Minecraft as a Non-Steam Game to Your Library"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>
Go to &amp;ldquo;Games&amp;rdquo; -&amp;gt; &amp;ldquo;Add a Non-Steam Game to My Library&amp;rdquo; -&amp;gt; &amp;ldquo;Browse&amp;rdquo; and add the Minecraft Launcher. In my environment, it&amp;rsquo;s located on the D drive: &amp;ldquo;D:\XboxGames\Minecraft Launcher\Content\gamelaunchhelper.exe&amp;rdquo;.
After opening, ensure &amp;ldquo;gamelaunchhelper&amp;rdquo; is checked and click &amp;ldquo;Add Selected Programs&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="remote-play-from-your-laptop-steam-link-client">Remote Play from your Laptop (Steam Link Client)
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;em>Make sure Steam is closed on your laptop. It will interfere with the connection.&lt;/em>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m32s090.webp"
width="1920"
height="1080"
srcset="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m32s090_hu_a3609bf88c545148.webp 480w, https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-11h21m32s090_hu_31df4914216907c4.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Launching Steam Link"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>
Launch Steam Link.
Allow access if prompted by the firewall.
You may need to click an OK button on your gaming PC the first time you connect.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The mouse cursor might not appear. Connecting a spare mouse to the gaming PC can resolve this. Alternatively, if you are using Windows 11 Pro, logging in and out of a remote desktop session can also make the cursor appear.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-12h03m53s138.webp"
width="1920"
height="1080"
srcset="https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-12h03m53s138_hu_fa43f70dc3ee5298.webp 480w, https://takoyakisoft.com/p/steam-link-play-minecraft-remotely-smooth-gameplay-on-your-laptop/vlcsnap-2024-11-20-12h03m53s138_hu_cebee1720a025208.webp 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="Disable Raw Mouse Input in Minecraft"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="177"
data-flex-basis="426px"
>
It&amp;rsquo;s recommended to disable Raw Mouse Input in Minecraft&amp;rsquo;s settings. For some reason, moving the mouse cursor while opening and closing a chest could cause the viewpoint to shift in that direction. Disabling Raw Mouse Input should resolve this issue.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>